    <body>
        
        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName><hi rend="print">6<hi rend="superscript">A</hi>, Rue Royale | Bruxelles</hi></placeName>
                    <date>March 25 1879</date>
                    <salute>Dear Sir</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
                    <p>I hope you will excuse me for not answering your exceedingly kind letter earlier, especially as you honor me with a request for my photograph; but I had not one left.<ref target="#foot.f1"/> I have just received the first copy of a new one, of which I respectfully beg your acceptance. Were it not too presuming, I would venture to ask for yours; this favor I hope you will grant.</p>
                    <p>Your very kind words are a great encouragement for my friend Gevaert and self, and we feel most proud to receive this consecration of yours on our first steps in Science.<ref target="#foot.f2"/></p>
<p>Yours gratefully | Leo Errera</p> 
                </div>
            </div>
            
            
            
        </div>
        
        
        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">See <ref target="./DCP-LETT-11928.xml">letter to L. A. Errera, 13 March 1879</ref> and n. 4. The photograph of Errera has not been found.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f2">CD had praised <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_10022.xml">Errera and Gevaert 1878</ref>; <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_1856.xml">Gustave Gevaert</ref> was the paper’s co-author (see <ref target="./DCP-LETT-11928.xml">letter to L. A. Errera, 13 March 1879</ref>).</note>  
        </div>  
      
